sentences: In 2016, FKi 1st released his own EP, First Time For Everything, on Mad Decent and toured with Fetty Wap, Post Malone, Justin Bieber, Diplo, and others.
He was also executive producer of Post Malone's debut album, Stoney (2016), which later went 3× platinum.
In 2009, FKi shared studio space with Jon Jon Traxx, Iggy Azalea (then known by her birth name, Amethyst Kelly), and Natalie Sims.
In 2012, FKi met American EDM producer Diplo, at a small local club in Atlanta and introduced him to Iggy Azalea.
In 2014, FKi 1st met Post Malone and came out with "White Iverson".
It was released on SoundCloud and received one million plays within three weeks.

In August 2015 he opened for Rita Ora at the El Rey theatre in Los Angeles and Drais Beach Club in Las Vegas.
In 2016 FKi 1st released his solo EP First Time For Everything on Mad Decent.
In April, FKi 1st joined Diplo & Friends at the Heineken House at Coachella.
FKi 1st was the executive producer for Post Malone's debut album Stoney, and has recently collaborated with artists Njomza, Party Favor, Nicki Minaj, 2 Chainz, Anne Dereaux, and more.
In February 2018 he started the Good Gas series of albums featuring artists such as 2 Chainz, ASAP Ferg, and MadeinTYO.
He released the album Tokyo Project in December 2019.
FKi went on to produce Iggy Azalea's entire TrapGold and in 2012 served as the official DJs for her European tour.
